cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new logic, XPL, for expressing properties of probabilistic transition systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with Recursive Markov Decision Processes (RMDPs), which are commonly used in AI applications. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper proposes a model checking procedure for XPL. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the termination of Recursive Markov Chains (RMCs) and Recursive Markov Decision Processes (RMDPs), which are stochastic processes commonly studied in the field of algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper deals with specifying properties of reactive probabilistic systems, which is relevant to software engineering.
